This paper is about improving end-to-end attention models for speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses pretraining and training techniques, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper uses LSTM language models, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning). The use of CTC loss function and attention-based models also suggests the possibility of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SD (Sound) categories.
